ZIMA-CAD-Sync
=============

Requirements
------------
Qt 4.x, 5.x - modules core, gui and network (widgets, ftp), qmake
QuaZIP - http://quazip.sourceforge.net/
Thunderbird for the feature "Send by mail" to work

Installation
------------
  tar xzf ZIMA-CAD-Sync-1.2.0-src.tar.gz
  cd ZIMA-CAD-Sync-1.2.0-src
  qmake
  make

Now you've got executable ZIMA-CAD-Sync, you can move it to /usr/local/bin
or wherever you want.

Useful information
------------------
System context menu works only in Windows. You have to run it once
as admin so it can create the menu in registry.

If you want to use translations, you have to put the translation file
next to ZIMA-CAD-Sync executable or to subdir 'locale', otherwise it won't
be found. ZIMA-CAD-Sync tries to load the language your system is using.
